item.title: Just starting off
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

expozee:

http://prntscr.com/2eii6q it shows this now :palm:

The problem is you use the java variable which doesn’t update since you installed only the JDK, you can either install JRE which is nothing more then the JVM or you can update the java environment variables path to point to the JVM in your JDK folder. Another step would be to just install netbeans or eclipse which will take care of the running and compiling set up for you when you work on your server.
